cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper discusses large-scale supervised classification algorithms based on deep convolutional neural networks (DCNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the task of adaptively finding concise training subsets, which involves optimization methods and feedback from the current performance of the classifier, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper mentions that their approach can make the classifier more robust in the presence of label noise and class imbalance, which could also place it in the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
